/cpgAfX2Imx1Din\naBTD3EjEUFNgtF1XKv3DXulvkaAvB8+JFdUQp8ThQno+om5JfkW/53l2+Zi2H+i7\nh9K4DJUSARo6UiuDjQQxWeEtcrDzWqcnS7qHZtmFQdvavPBWKVuVBQ0R+5ZPbcWb\nS65X6Sfqcuih4j5TvJs468wrYJkuHGUeE+2gre2gqUTr0i6dzKA9lx8kgl+cxMz2\nYyl5KvKp3bhqWC0CQ9wDrLpxsgykV3TtNkwbV8d1jqONTKyS8jp7VMvIDy+avz9X\nDvEQleZhq8VRuYHYBQxZ7pcGwDepc9mAsaqCOawtRYoed4EktFSXjqAgbmqUpgQo\n5BJoP2Ldy7iE5aH5+xtj\n=HQCR\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----\n","payload":"tree 8000ab74f2d1c8067709f95d35ec4cd5d41877b5\nparent 04d408b29d059f131766448265768ce705801aaf\nauthor Puneet Dixit <puneetdixit4321@gmail.com> 1779395051 +0530\ncommitter GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1779395051 +0200\n\nfix: remove raw-text hydration markers (#18269)\n\nFixes #14413.\n\nThis keeps the temporary raw-text hydration sentinel used by dynamic\n`<svelte:element>` from becoming part of the final DOM. Hydration still\ngets a marker to advance through for raw-text children, but the marker\nis removed after the child renderer runs, so `<style>` and `<script>`\ncontents stay identical to SSR output.\n\nTests:\n- `pnpm test hydration -t svelte-head-dynamic-style`\n- `pnpm test hydration`\n- `pnpm test runtime-runes -t svelte-element`\n- `pnpm lint`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Puneet Dixit <236133619+puneetdixit200@users.noreply.github.com>\nCo-authored-by: Simon H <5968653+dummdidumm@users.noreply.github.com>","verified_at":"2026-05-21T20:24:12Z"}},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/commits/8b961be0b190078815219e614b739b170e1087b1","html_url":"https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/commit/8b961be0b190078815219e614b739b170e1087b1","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/commits/8b961be0b190078815219e614b739b170e1087b1/comments","author":{"login":"puneetdixit200","id":236133619,"node_id":"U_kgDODhMc8w","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/236133619?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/puneetdixit200","html_url":"https://github.com/puneetdixit200","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/puneetdixit200/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/puneetdixit200/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/puneetdixit200/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/puneetdixit200/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/puneetdixit200/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/puneetdixit200/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/puneetdixit200/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/puneetdixit200/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/puneetdixit200/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"committer":{"login":"web-flow","id":19864447,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE5ODY0NDQ3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/19864447?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow","html_url":"https://github.com/web-flow","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"parents":[{"sha":"04d408b29d059f131766448265768ce705801aaf","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/commits/04d408b29d059f131766448265768ce705801aaf","html_url":"https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/commit/04d408b29d059f131766448265768ce705801aaf"}]},{"sha":"04d408b29d059f131766448265768ce705801aaf","node_id":"C_kwDOBG2gSdoAKDA0ZDQwOGIyOWQwNTlmMTMxNzY2NDQ4MjY1NzY4Y2U3MDU4MDFhYWY","commit":{"author":{"name":"Mathias Picker","email":"48158184+MathiasWP@users.noreply.github.com","date":"2026-05-21T19:53:34Z"},"committer":{"name":"GitHub","email":"noreply@github.com","date":"2026-05-21T19:53:34Z"},"message":"perf: walk composedPath() directly in delegated event propagation (#18268)\n\n## Summary\n\nThe propagation walk in `handle_event_propagation` already calls\n`event.composedPath()` at the start to find the entry index, but then\nre-derives the same chain step-by-step via `current_target.assignedSlot\n|| current_target.parentNode || .host`. Three property reads per\niteration is measurable on the hot event path.\n\nWalk the captured `path` array by index instead.\n\n## Notes on behavior\n\n`composedPath()` is the spec-compliant snapshot of the dispatch chain:\n- Same shadow-DOM crossings (slots and shadow roots are included for\ncomposed events).\n- Same `host` traversal (composed-path crosses shadow boundaries when\nappropriate).\n- Differs from the previous walk in one edge case: if a handler removes\na parent mid-dispatch, the snapshot-based walk continues through the\ncaptured chain (matches native browser semantics — the previous\n`parentNode` walk would have stopped at a null parent).\n\n## Performance\n\nMeasured in real Chromium on a click through a 30-deep tree with five\ndelegated handlers: **~245k hz → ~277k hz** (~+13%, ~−12% per-event\ntime).\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] All 6006 runtime tests pass (runtime-runes + runtime-legacy +\nruntime-browser)\n- [x] Native shadow-DOM event tests (in runtime-browser) pass unchanged\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>","tree":{"sha":"02bf647237e2e6459b044bb296b4399d28ef56d1","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/git/trees/02bf647237e2e6459b044bb296b4399d28ef56d1"},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/git/commits/04d408b29d059f131766448265768ce705801aaf","comment_count":0,"verification":{"verified":true,"reason":"valid","signature":"-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsFcBAABCAAQBQJqD2K+CRC1aQ7uu5UhlAAAtMQQABzHYYOepInMcCFRI1u+Dvkm\n0+GlXtgGfaTu63IJVYDQ8UWVIQl2lBcC4gbveISEzNYvNFg25jwgZv30d5lmVOAr\nu31aVu7nvqJCkKm6wvn1qvU0HPm9l3BgNVVky4mTPPinaWJkhafOmPaafF169ZaO\nKRi8bmTgi4PNhhDQJX9vwo0MVdGYQw67hKQ3dELTZt6Zs5uPUJx/w/aRbG/X1V1P\n3ozNYETQpblWhNQa7KDJf4WaV5QyCj/t68T+F1nPOXBS2Lx2sidHlwanw1c4c+pL\nsT9oZseyfbkioO7w3VLKO4tFuZK7A4FvRqbYu52HYqbFtxFo6IUlKGqXeslVLOpe\nAHBA+DIHlBHfymO2gC31ycc0/r2VnR8ZSj0pvOP5k80kAXn0BTWIAexg2JYD60U3\nEJGXXO+UhNDyR79nmVcQ9NFbAW1rtNdAq4zaYIMFn1OeSzAHBr59Vh5DFk5akEOJ\nplu57jNG/it9AdHfnTHZZfXhAOyiOv4mZtvHwFKlHKC7qWThA41lq1O4JtIvCrRF\ndEeQQ2wH01gy2f8tkk26P3qtzE6rJFrDjJEw8fm6GC5T69doPYswGvO2gICvRIfd\ngYI0bs5W4qw3eJAIwe9soIRivnzqdhw+Xe0kCHKxocxZ1eSb0oyqbj0cdq4ZMavx\nm2nLrg1f/sIedWrSuKEw\n=jbXK\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----\n","payload":"tree 02bf647237e2e6459b044bb296b4399d28ef56d1\nparent 078f901f611237d4c6fed16ef894f33572f9ccba\nauthor Mathias Picker <48158184+MathiasWP@users.noreply.github.com> 1779393214 +0200\ncommitter GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1779393214 +0200\n\nperf: walk composedPath() directly in delegated event propagation (#18268)\n\n## Summary\n\nThe propagation walk in `handle_event_propagation` already calls\n`event.composedPath()` at the start to find the entry index, but then\nre-derives the same chain step-by-step via `current_target.assignedSlot\n|| current_target.parentNode || .host`. Three property reads per\niteration is measurable on the hot event path.\n\nWalk the captured `path` array by index instead.\n\n## Notes on behavior\n\n`composedPath()` is the spec-compliant snapshot of the dispatch chain:\n- Same shadow-DOM crossings (slots and shadow roots are included for\ncomposed events).\n- Same `host` traversal (composed-path crosses shadow boundaries when\nappropriate).\n- Differs from the previous walk in one edge case: if a handler removes\na parent mid-dispatch, the snapshot-based walk continues through the\ncaptured chain (matches native browser semantics — the previous\n`parentNode` walk would have stopped at a null parent).\n\n## Performance\n\nMeasured in real Chromium on a click through a 30-deep tree with five\ndelegated handlers: **~245k hz → ~277k hz** (~+13%, ~−12% per-event\ntime).\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] All 6006 runtime tests pass (runtime-runes + runtime-legacy +\nruntime-browser)\n- [x] Native shadow-DOM event tests (in runtime-browser) pass unchanged\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>","verified_at":"2026-05-21T19:53:34Z"}},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/commits/04d408b29d059f131766448265768ce705801aaf","html_url":"https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/commit/04d408b29d059f131766448265768ce705801aaf","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/commits/04d408b29d059f131766448265768ce705801aaf/comments","author":{"login":"MathiasWP","id":48158184,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ4MTU4MTg0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/48158184?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/MathiasWP","html_url":"https://github.com/MathiasWP","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MathiasWP/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MathiasWP/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MathiasWP/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MathiasWP/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MathiasWP/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MathiasWP/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MathiasWP/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MathiasWP/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MathiasWP/received_events","type":"User","u