s.noreply.github.com","date":"2026-05-21T18:25:51Z"},"committer":{"name":"GitHub","email":"noreply@github.com","date":"2026-05-21T18:25:51Z"},"message":"fix: correctly coordinate component-level effects inside async blocks (#18260)\n\nWhile looking at the reproduction in\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/issues/18221#issuecomment-4497918414\nI immediately got greeted with a runtime error when running it in the\nplayground (weirdly not in the Stackblitz version). The error was that a\ncomponent expected a binding to be set in onMount, but the timing of\nonMount was wrong.\n\nTurns out it's because our logic to determine whether or not to defer\ntop level effects is flawed. `REACTION_RAN`, which was used previously,\nis already set if the initialized component is inside an async block. We\ninstead check for `component_context.i` which is set to `true` on\n`pop()`.","tree":{"sha":"5b1a50f9b7b8a60975627b99b99a590fae9231fb","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/git/trees/5b1a50f9b7b8a60975627b99b99a590fae9231fb"},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/git/commits/91a42e2ed6bda52205b269d28e70b9d15cd87292","comment_count":0,"verification":{"verified":true,"reason":"valid","signature":"-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsFcBAABCAAQBQJqD04vCRC1aQ7uu5UhlAAAMrYQAHyoeJJKleJdrGU4rnTV0vfq\ngLVbdKQynsIjvpojPKFarYBOVt9A6HoAGHnFXXmm7MX5MHuZrevsQBhtOTF7ueV+\n3x4L0lPXnpOVQO5GLtbHUMUH9ueDSn+CnGPCl0mTpWvtkHgjApaH/xDXs6QFVvLo\nhxfuPFgEu/M99XBv/+jrOo4BSgJIpgeSk8lJfzwd9SXPiIaEcNrye9X6eTQSCUz1\nLyTxhXVueMQHmui/hhGel3Enbx1I+faxIhQXdsQX0V5btwiU6dvBnMfORiWkchdT\ntUH4tPrVrTz1UauduaGHCCM6llyYofx+AV5JWhwFWkS9wL6ZSOwQ1y7PndGvs7RF\neRpdnCEG2lGACJIS6IkT1cZdebHXlqzCzp5fe0SDa0ZX8fyHWd/f2LIXvqc9LtOK\n/mTaCi/wu+sKRoF/LIsXGeZb535Ji4boiqNwyBiP9L3FsZ0jyajAw0uyPbE3LHmV\nPTkHm8qGkustjCIOnP/sR7ZpHf4/Zk+0Ez1JdNNk/76v4K/tIqvVhyHWERs4gxwZ\nb87Y38EYPgnu2CFu7QefczImhP6l4N1z2A476Atz1djycxsWgrsP5uwB3kJM/ZLS\nyEXlAOdF/iFJmPnJSy5CarBOi6AoSVhAOwHApaTyvZMSjNHmGFH05BrBr4UuAn7R\nirasfkV7GB86DyVH+HM8\n=trj/\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----\n","payload":"tree 5b1a50f9b7b8a60975627b99b99a590fae9231fb\nparent 65283bc13a54c41ee96940b559c1a027b8770882\nauthor Simon H <5968653+dummdidumm@users.noreply.github.com> 1779387951 +0200\ncommitter GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1779387951 +0200\n\nfix: correctly coordinate component-level effects inside async blocks (#18260)\n\nWhile looking at the reproduction in\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/issues/18221#issuecomment-4497918414\nI immediately got greeted with a runtime error when running it in the\nplayground (weirdly not in the Stackblitz version). The error was that a\ncomponent expected a binding to be set in onMount, but the timing of\nonMount was wrong.\n\nTurns out it's because our logic to determine whether or not to defer\ntop level effects is flawed. `REACTION_RAN`, which was used previously,\nis already set if the initialized component is inside an async block. We\ninstead check for `component_context.i` which is set to `true` on\n`pop()`.","verified_at":"2026-05-21T18:25:52Z"}},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/commits/91a42e2ed6bda52205b269d28e70b9d15cd87292","html_url":"https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/commit/91a42e2ed6bda52205b269d28e70b9d15cd87292","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/commits/91a42e2ed6bda52205b269d28e70b9d15cd87292/comments","author":{"login":"dummdidumm","id":5968653,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU5Njg2NTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5968653?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm","html_url":"https://github.com/dummdidumm","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/subscriptions","or