y.github.com","date":"2026-05-19T20:16:03Z"},"committer":{"name":"GitHub","email":"noreply@github.com","date":"2026-05-19T20:16:03Z"},"message":"fix: `{#await await ...}` and async dependencies fixes (#18243)\n\nThis started out as an investigation to get rid of the runtime code for\n`{#await ...}` that deactivated a batch prior to reading the promise\nfunction. That can result in a new batch being created if the promise\ninvocation happens to write a source.\n\nThrough that I discovered two other bugs:\n1. The way we handle `{#await await ...}` was flawed around\nSSR/hydration: On the server it would await the expression (which it\nshould not; `{#await await ...}` is kind of a weird special case here)\nand during hydration it did not produce matching nodes, leading to\nhydration fails.\n2. When reading a dependency after an await expression which we add to\nthe current reaction, we did not deduplicate those reads. That can lead\nto duplicate dependencies, which in turn can lead to bugs when\n`remove_reaction` later runs. Conside this: You have `deps = [count,\nunrelated, count]`. Now you do `remove_reactions(deps, 1)`, i.e. \"remove\nall reactions after the first one\". That means the \"disconnect these\nfrom each other\" logic runs for `count`, too, because it's also in the\nthird position, but that is wrong because it is also in the first\nposition, i.e. the connection should be kept.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Rich Harris <rich.harris@vercel.com>","tree":{"sha":"e2b4237aaae61a10dde35e9e5323053b43620794","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/git/trees/e2b4237aaae61a10dde35e9e5323053b43620794"},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/git/commits/000c594e05d27e3e56c08cf30274689615d99092","comment_count":0,"verification":{"verified":true,"reason":"valid","signature":"-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsFcBAABCAAQBQJqDMUDCRC1aQ7uu5UhlAAAIeAQADWWTn8V2s1oeqEestTQm2Uf\nzuZL9I3UTfca46QOD0vfg6zOzFKsHzpT/lR459RYfdiZ3YaCjHl3yUU1cNC0juAw\nVDm/rfRDaAlr38s7KR3YF8aR601/SHldx/USEuHnRhvs15/hAFWmhFUA5MBZcwRX\nenFJgzsBfvZAnrzTqnmk/+lvtAsrLirVTkBdrA7lvgisO/KwM041XVRZxL5XOJkx\nzPWIrKQL48SB3aoJ+GbUa1ueW6aeerlXkxEXnl2kU3fzXX+iUhh4lFpx3vO4l5Fi\nRVEzBpj4aGrtAlsMm8blvSXaWPX63tcHnAiyRo2QqXTSn2mXXjrYe7Sle9GIUXQ8\nNiBpgj3UNp1GVDm9cmkwMGJl1EDU3nUNEfoty12gz4W5a3hZ41EJhodANDOs6vPB\nZz9wIdeC3oE1+lKMiLnAKiVUnmyQV7CIjAGW6hln+6VYaTQovV5o6LtLZdFpWpkE\nCwtHos721D4n30thzrfLbfV7JK9M31Wn299ZW1LZSEL/uOBlspg8wlBWi88l7PPQ\nDIxNsUhnbDLftgKFjSn2I70XCVQu+0bU5QHO5nGdWDXHNWoagF+CP02cZZxVdok5\nrXDS9rzRHKEwLPx4zL8g7UtEhuLy87gEa5GmHYUljys7ysv6J6yGUQZzTPy1LBkj\njtqOw6k1NWQJz8IEfIdk\n=to96\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----\n","payload":"tree e2b4237aaae61a10dde35e9e5323053b43620794\nparent be8ffeb2a4b0c36657fb5c1bdcf36971da814227\nauthor Simon H <5968653+dummdidumm@users.noreply.github.com> 1779221763 +0200\ncommitter GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1779221763 -0400\n\nfix: `{#await await ...}` and async dependencies fixes (#18243)\n\nThis started out as an investigation to get rid of the runtime code for\n`{#await ...}` that deactivated a batch prior to reading the promise\nfunction. That can result in a new batch being created if the promise\ninvocation happens to write a source.\n\nThrough that I discovered two other bugs:\n1. The way we handle `{#await await ...}` was flawed around\nSSR/hydration: On the server it would await the expression (which it\nshould not; `{#await await ...}` is kind of a weird special case here)\nand during hydration it did not produce matching nodes, leading to\nhydration fails.\n2. When reading a dependency after an await expression which we add to\nthe current reaction, we did not deduplicate those reads. That can lead\nto duplicate dependencies, which in turn can lead to bugs when\n`remove_reaction` later runs. Conside this: You have `deps = [count,\nunrelated, count]`. Now you do `remove_reactions(deps, 1)`, i.e. \"remove\nall reactions after the first one\". That means the \"disconnect these\nfrom each other\" logic runs for `count`, too, because it's also in the\nthird position, but that is wrong because it is also in the first\nposition, i.e. the connection should be kept.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Rich Harris <rich.harris@vercel.com>","verified_at":"2026-05-19T20:16:04Z"}},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/commits/000c594e05d27e3e56c08cf30274689615d99092","html_url":"https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/commit/000c594e05d27e3e56c08cf30274689615d99092","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/commits/000c594e05d27e3e56c08cf30274689615d99092/comments","author":{"login":"dummdidumm","id":5968653,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU5Njg2NTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5968653?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm","html_url":"https://github.com/dummdidumm","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dummdidumm/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"committer":{"login":"web-flow","id":19864447,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE5ODY0NDQ3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/19864447?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow","html_url":"https://github.com/web-flow","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/gis