Fixes #10031.\n- [x] Prefix your PR title with `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, or `docs:`.\n- [x] This message body should clearly illustrate what problems it\nsolves.\n- [x] Ideally, include a test that fails without this PR but passes with\nit.\n- [x] If this PR changes code within `packages/svelte/src`, add a\nchangeset (`npx changeset`).\n\n### What this changes\n\nServer attribute template generation currently wraps each dynamic\nexpression in `$.stringify`, even when the compiler can prove the\nexpression is a string or a known constant. This reuses the existing\nscope evaluation metadata so server output can avoid `$.stringify` for\nproven string/constant chunks while keeping it for possibly nullish\nunknown values.\n\nThe updated snapshot covers a mixed attribute with a known string,\nmutable state, `null`, numeric/undefined constants, a known\nstring-producing `typeof`, and an unknown prop value.\n\n### Tests and linting\n\n- [x] `pnpm test snapshot -t nullish-coallescence-omittance`\n- [x] `pnpm test snapshot`\n- [x] `pnpm --filter svelte check`\n- [x] `pnpm lint`\n- [x] `pnpm prettier --check .changeset/slow-bikes-serve.md`\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Rich Harris <hello@rich-harris.dev>","tree":{"sha":"6b53e73b1c0bae1bd9850f9e6f871afef2ba2389","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/git/trees/6b53e73b1c0bae1bd9850f9e6f871afef2ba2389"},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/git/commits/a5df6616ea6c8ee0984ff0fc7b04e51472f1d01d","comment_count":0,"verification":{"verified":true,"reason":"valid","signature":"-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsFcBAABCAAQBQJqC2AWCRC1aQ7uu5UhlAAAk94QAFxwIozaj3cOV7NhUeOu7sPo\n7RmB5p04R0GpVgRgqbvfiA7gEeKA4kGyUjTBokN8u4NYy/0mYjO/keb7WNXAZSBi\nXkxsyk8QmlMSBWTKmqvCjB1COU+5+iiY+v/0mo3b4Q8uhWbq7riUFayVr/ZG83On\nkX/sG7YK37R7O6T0Tsd4d/yJzghSkgJN/m4OD5Zj31LfJiW/qk2LzHuB60spXhaj\nuAoGiDePIJyiOavLw8V3AVBeQ8trU6HOD1Gc0kCo3QXFL5VDMe3SQobE4ANomIYK\nEhpUfmJB43Kl7c8ylF0zuORNnFwShWRTNkr4znhjP62UKhxUbSBC6ZIzSwpKeAm7\nVu09Qm