vacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"parents":[{"sha":"eb10a70cf1f003c3e93f3c4ecc9749870e7581c6","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/commits/eb10a70cf1f003c3e93f3c4ecc9749870e7581c6","html_url":"https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/commit/eb10a70cf1f003c3e93f3c4ecc9749870e7581c6"}]},{"sha":"eb10a70cf1f003c3e93f3c4ecc9749870e7581c6","node_id":"C_kwDOBG2gSdoAKGViMTBhNzBjZjFmMDAzYzNlOTNmM2M0ZWNjOTc0OTg3MGU3NTgxYzY","commit":{"author":{"name":"Simon H","email":"5968653+dummdidumm@users.noreply.github.com","date":"2026-05-18T15:36:17Z"},"committer":{"name":"GitHub","email":"noreply@github.com","date":"2026-05-18T15:36:17Z"},"message":"fix: unset context synchronously in `run` (#18236)\n\nOur `run` function which executes top level awaits (and synchronous\nstatements in-between/after) did not unset the context in time in case\nthe function returns an async value. In that case the context was still\naround until the that promise resolves, which can be too late because\nunrelated things can be intertwined with the batch.\n\nThe test shows this: Without the fix, the unrelated count incrementation\nwould not update the view until the top level awaits in the child are\ndone. In the test this just shows as a delayed visual update, but it\nalso can result in stale roots as shown in\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/issues/18221#issuecomment-4470921077","tree":{"sha":"f3d7bb01bcbc7cc47b657a39bdf2de71c1421696","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/git/trees/f3d7bb01bcbc7cc47b657a39bdf2de71c1421696"},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/svelte/git/commits/eb10a70cf1f003c3e93f3c4ecc9749870e7581c6","comment_count":0,"verification":{"verified":true,"reason":"valid","signature":"-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsFcBAABCAAQBQJqCzHxCRC1aQ7uu5UhlAAAPd8QAEEeISGZHN9GKhv9PX+Ui3MW\nvtkoiuIXxVtFSHnlMn7ZOLtWQJxyJnQK4RRNCXKH+pJcHc3sdRX9RaciXcUUdZtA\n